    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It turns out the current main branch of Python has swapped the numbers of `PY_MONITORING_EVENT_PY_UNWIND` and `PY_MONITORING_EVENT_RAISE` and so this affects what we see when we sort and print the events.\n\nhttps://github.com/python/cpython/issues/142186\nhttps://github.com/python/cpython/pull/146182\n\nIt's obviously a trivial change and nothing is really broken. The numbers are probably supposed to be opaque, so I guess they can swap them any time they like between minor releases. However, to me it looks like it might have just been a left over part of an earlier version and not strictly necessary.\n\nTherefore I've asked nicely. So it's probably worth waiting to see before rewriting the test.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:55Z",
